My sister @maliabianchimau and I fell in love with these bags when we first saw them. They are handwoven by local artisans, naturally dyed, and made out of 100 percent natural grass fibers from Colombia. We ended up buying some extra because we thought they were so beautiful and we are finally ready to sell them! If interested, we will be selling them first come first serve. DM me your name, color preference, Venmo handle and shipping address. Domestic orders only. Because of the nature of handmade products there are slight variations with color and shape and each bag is one of a kind.  They are hand woven from The Kankuamo indigenous people from the eastern slope of the Sierra Nevada of Santa Marta. They use the technique of hand weaving with eye needle. These bags are ethically sourced from this group and help support their community as well as this traditional technique. We have limited supply so first come first serve. Thank you! All sales final.
